BLUR has always been one of those bands that were on a different level. Their music, art direction, and overall vibe was sophisticated yet raw and unapologetic. Coffee & TV might be one of my favorite music videos of all time. 

I’m beyond proud to announce PLEASURES limited collaboration with the Britpop icons @blurofficial. This collection focuses on the self- titled album featuring choice cuts like Beetlebum and Song 2. In just a few weeks, BLUR is having their reunion shows at Wembley Stadium to a sold out crowd of 90,000. Full collection available Friday on www.pleasuresnow.com

——— On the tenth episode of the August Forum Podcast, we are joined by esteemed creative director, music curator, and PLEASURES (@pleasures) co-founder, Alex James (@ayejames). From his time exploring music subcultures in a variety of different genres to his curation of polarizing graphics, Alex shines in his industry and his passion is clear in everything he does. On this episode we take a deeper dive into his skills as a creative and personable nature has allowed him to develop a powerhouse in the streetwear culture with PLEASURES. We also dive into the upcoming August x PLEASURES collaboration. This is The August Forum. Listen now via link in bio

Growing up in New Jersey, our latest Pirate Radio feature started life thrifting for gems while expanding and synthesizing his knowledge of clothing and music. Alternate culture is at the centre of Pleasures. Combining a lifelong relationship with music, alongside a zeal for challenging norms, the brand stands out as a unique and forward-thinking brand. 

Co-founder and designer Alex James maintains an unyielding ideology that cannot be challenged

Go to www.thepopmanifesto.com to read our conversation with Alex James and how is working towards building @pleasures into a fashion powerhouse.

Interview by @ilirjana
